 African prosecutor requested for the Palestinian Authority (PA) to clarify statements made by its President, Mahmoud Abbas, following his announcement of breaking all agreements with Isreal  which included security cooperation. This recent sanction is yet another obstacle placed in the way of the ongoing investigation as the Gambian national had already seen her US visa revoked last year, but had, nevertheless, carried on fearlessly with her professional duties citing her “independent and impartial mandate” despite blatant opposition from the Trump administration. The ICC, of which Washington is not a member, is an international court to try war crimes and crimes against humanity. Africa News Vanguard International war crimes judges ruled on Thursday that a probe into wartime abuses in Afghanistan must go ahead, including looking into possible atrocities committed by US forces, as they overturned a previous court ruling. The call was immediately hailed by human rights organisations as a "pivotal moment" for victims of… March 5, 2020 In "Foreign" In the preliminary investigation already done by the Office of the Prosecutor of the ICC headed by the Chief Prosecutor, Ms Fatou Bensouda, over the war crimes and crimes against humanity committed in the course of the violence, six cases have reportedly been established against the terrorists. December 21, 2018 In "Editorial" A decision on whether to open a formal investigation of potential war crimes committed in Afghanistan since 2003, including possible wrongdoing by U.S. personnel, has been delayed. July 5, 2017 In "News"